What are annotations in java ? what is there primary purpose ?

Ans) Annotations in java are basically meta data which gives information about other parts
 of code like methods, classes, fields, constructors, warnings etc., These annotations
 doesn't effect other parts of the code but useful while documenting the code. These
 annotations are prefixed with @ symbol.

 Difference between annotations and comments ?
 ans) Annotations are a form of meta data which can be processed by tools. Whereas,
 comments are used for human readability purposes and are completely ignored at run time
 and compile time.

 @Deprecated, @SuppressedWarnings, @Override are some of the inbuilt annotations in java.
